<p>GDP growth: 3.0% GDP: $518bn (PPP: $1,007bn) Inflation: 1.7% Population: 23.3m GDP per head: $22,170 (PPP: $43,120)</p>

<p>The year will open with parliamentary and presidential elections; the outcome will hang on the opposition Democratic Progressive Party's ability to satisfy a public appetite for rapprochement with the mainland without betraying its pro-independence roots. The ruling Kuomintang will be hard to shift, given the strong economy and the generally positive reception for its cross-strait policies; it is likely to retain power. Reduced exports will slow growth.</p>

